text: in the early morning of November 29th
North Korea launched a new type of
missile it's called the hua Seong 15 and
it is a monster nuclear experts say it's
far bigger more advanced and more
destructive than any missile ever tested
by the rogue regime and with this
intercontinental ballistic missile North
Korea could potentially strike any city
in the United States after a two-month
pause in missile testing Kim jong-un
defied u.s. threats and sanctions by
personally ordering and overseeing the
launch experts say that images released
by North Korea shows several big
advances over the two ICBMs tested
earlier in 2017
there's a heftier transporter launcher
vehicle that allows for mobile launches
those are harder to detect a rounded
nose cone that in Russian and American
ICBMs allows missiles to carry multiple
warheads and a new two engine design for
the initial flight stage that boosts the
missiles range the missile flew for over
53 minutes before landing in the Sea of
Japan 600 miles to the east of Pyongyang
in a real attack the missile would have
an estimated 8,000 mile range but
experts say it's unclear if a missile on
an attack course armed with a real
warhead could survive re-entry into the
atmosphere still North Korean state
media was not surprisingly triumphant it
claimed the new missile marked the
completion of the rocket weaponry system
the regime's been developing for decades
